metadata.name: Fracture #70
metadata.description:
Fragments of fragments, pieced together.


Please be patient as previews may take a while to generate.
Press 's' in live view to save the current image.
You can modify the URL to specify an image size. Keep in mind that the color palette, styles, and general look of the piece will generally remain the same, but a new image will be created to fit the new dimensions. To do this, add x and y URL parameters to the end of the URL. (Images are created using a pixel ratio of 2, so adding ?x=2560&y1440 to the end of the URL will actually create a 5120x2880 image.)

metadata.name: rive #562
metadata.description:
Starting with a repeatable system of colors and/or triangles typically seen in geometric abstraction, rive employs generative art to break/split/rive those patterns‚Äìand the comfort we find in them‚Äìin slight, seemingly unintentional ways.  With each subsequent split, our comfort fades as the artwork is shredded into barely recognizable fragments of a once carefully orchestrated pattern.

Not all rivings are created equal; some are subtle and barely visible while others are acute and violent.  

What holds it together is what breaks it apart.  

created using triangles and p5js

rive
abstractment, 2022

metadata.name: Digital Organics #9
metadata.description:
Digital Organics seeks to infuse an organic soul into binary code. A flow of digital current passing through an algorithm, rendering a synthetic version of nature.

A few notes: due to its synthetic nature, it will look more detailed in fullscreen. And it is recommended to use this mode to be able to fully enjoy the whole spectrum of details.

A static version can be obtained by using the keypress 's'. 

An additional hyper-saturated mode can be accessed through the keypress 'h'.

metadata.name: The Space Inside #222
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press ‚Äôp‚Äô to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare
- 9% to have a soft monochrome and color palette

metadata.name: Consequence Broadcast [Speed Run] #79
metadata.description:
a.k.a. Reaction Diffusion. The canvas is a grid of cells, each containing some amount of A and some amount of B. Every step, A and B react with each other and diffuse into neighbouring cells. The amounts of diffusion and reaction have different settings, which can vary across the canvas or over time. Then, cool things happen with colours. 

This is an experimental project, created as part of a Speed Run over ~37 hours in one weekend (I did also sleep and eat in that time. I even went for a walk. Go me). 
- It requires WEBGL2 and is GPU intensive. 
- There may be slight discrepancies in the patterns on different devices, due to rounding. 

Big thanks to everyone who followed along/offered advice and especially to Piter Pasma who helped me out with the noise dithering code that took everything to the next dimension.

Press P to pause.
Press 1-5 to alter speed.

metadata.name: Flow #141
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022
